# Connect to bandit0
ssh bandit0@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
# Password: bandit0

# List files in current directory
ls

# Read the readme file
cat readme

# Connect to next level
ssh bandit1@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
# Password: [REDACTED]


Solution
The readme file contains the password for bandit1. Simple cat command reveals the contents.
Key Learnings

Basic SSH connection syntax
ls command for listing directory contents
cat command for reading file contents
Understanding the home directory concept
